FBIS3-36905 "drsov028_b_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-028 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Feb 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Media Issues 40 Percent of Listeners Affected by Radio Strike LD1002130694 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 1100 GMT 10 Feb 94 LD1002130694 Moscow Russian Television Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [From the "Vesti" newscast] [Text] Russia's own television and radio journalists will, it seems, also have to unite, but for a different reason. They will have to join forces with their viewers in order to defend the broadcasting industry. We continue to receive reports from regions where programs from Moscow are no longer being received. ITAR-TASS has reported that 40 percent of listeners could no longer hear radio programs by noon.
